ly. The meaning could be ‘meeting’. In North America, it may also be a shortened form of some other name.","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 艾, referring to ‘Chinese mugwort’, a type of plant used in traditional Chinese medical treatment: (i) perhaps from the second element of Ru Ai (汝艾), the name of an official who lived during the reign of Shao Kang, the 6th king of the Xia dynasty (2070–1600  BC ). (ii) from the first element of the placename Ai Ling (艾陵), the name of a hill (located in Shandong province), the fief of Ai Kong (艾孔), an official in the state of Qi during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ). (iii) from the placename Ai (艾), the name of a fief (located in Jiangxi province) which was granted to an official in the state of Chu during the Spring and Autumn period (770–476  BC ). (iv) adopted as a surname by the Qu Jin (去斤), Qu Ai (去艾), and Ai Jin (艾斤) families from the Xianbei ethnic group in northern China during the Northern Wei dynasty (386–534  AD ). (v) from Ai (艾), the name of an ancient state (possibly in present-day Jiangxi province) during the Shang dynasty (1600–1046  BC ).","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 愛, meaning ‘love’ in Chinese: (i) said to be traced back to Ai Xie Wu (愛邪勿), prime minister of the state of Huihu (known as Uyghur Empire or Uyghur Khaganate), who was endowed with the surname Ai (愛) by Emperor Wuzong of Tang (814–846  AD ). (ii) a Han Chinese surname for some members of the Aisin Gioro family from the Manchu ethnic group, known as the royal family of the Qing dynasty (1616 – 1911  AD ). (iii) a surname from minority ethnic groups in Taiwan."]}]},{"name":"Rhys","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Traditional name meaning ‘ardour’; borne in the Middle Ages by various rulers in south-west Wales, including  Rhys ap Tewdur  (  d. 1093 ) and  Rhys ap Gruffudd  (  1132–97 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Reece","meanings":["Anglicized spelling of Rhys . The name is now in widespread and frequent use outside Wales, in many cases representing a transferred use of the surname so spelled, which is derived from the given name."]},{"name":"Rees","meanings":["Anglicized spelling of Welsh Rhys, in some cases representing a transferred use of the surname so spelled, which is derived from the Welsh given name."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Rhys ab Arthfael King of Glywyssing was born in 1110, in Senghenydd, Glamorgan, Wales, his father, Ifor ap Meurig, was 26 and his mother, Gwladys Verch Ynyr, was 30. He had at least 5 sons and 1 daughter with Nest verch Gruffydd of Llandilo. He died in 1211, at the age of 101."},"et":{"1110–1211":"1110–1211","1130–1211":"1130–1211","1120–1197":"1120–1197","1122–Female":"1122–Surnud","1130–Female":"1130–Surnud","1140–1211":"1140–1211","1150–1211":"1150–1211","1152–Male":"1152–Surnud","1154–Male":"1154–Surnud","1085–Male":"1085–Surnud","1080–Female":"1080–Surnud","1080":"1080","1110":"1110","1154":"1154","1197":"1197","1120":"1120","1130":"1130","1152":"1152","1140":"1140","1085":"1085","1150":"1150","ABT 1130":"umbes 1130","1211":"1211","1122":"1122","Wales, United Kingdom":"Wales, United Kingdom","Glamorganshire, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom","Plâs Ifor, Ynysgynwraidd, Monmouthshire, England":"Skenfrith, Monmouthshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Wales":"Wales, United Kingdom","Senghenydd, Gwlad Morgan, Wales":"Senghenydd, Glamorgan, Wales","Senghennydd, Glamorgansire Wales":"Senghenydd, Glamorgan, Wales"},"fi":{"1110–1211":"1110–1211","1130–1211":"1130–1211","1120–1197":"1120–1197","1122–Female":"1122–Kuollut","1130–Female":"1130–Kuollut","1140–1211":"1140–1211","1150–1211":"1150–1211","1152–Male":"1152–Kuollut","1154–Male":"1154–Kuollut","1085–Male":"1085–Kuollut","1080–Female":"1080–Kuollut","1080":"1080","1110":"1110","1154":"1154","1197":"1197","1120":"1120","1130":"1130","1152":"1152","1140":"1140","1085":"1085","1150":"1150","ABT 1130":"noin 1130","1211":"12